HEADWORD: Intercipient
<hw>In`ter*cip"i*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intercipiens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>intercipere</ets>. See <er>Intercept</er>.]</ety>
<def>Intercepting; stopping.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One who,
or that which, intercepts or stops anything on the passage.</def></def2>
<rj><au>Wiseman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

